        <h2 id="verdict">Is SpyFu worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For SEO professionals and agencies: yes.</strong> SpyFu's core data is reliable and the workflows scale across multiple clients. The math works when you bill clients $2K–$10K/mo for SEO.</p>

        <p><strong>For content teams with writers: yes, with a caveat.</strong> SpyFu gives you keyword targets and the competitive landscape. You will still need a writing workflow and (in most cases) a content optimisation tool on top.</p>

        <p><strong>For small business owners: almost always no.</strong> You open SpyFu. You see your competitor ranks for hundreds of keywords and you find dozens of opportunities. You cannot write that much content this month. You cannot write a tenth of it. The data is accurate. The execution is impossible without a team. You would spend $39/mo watching your competitors win.</p>

